comments: Ferguson (OKC) moves legally alongside Lowry (TOR) and does not deliver contact during Lowry's drive.
Ibaka (TOR) is in a legal picking position as he is firmed up and does not deliver contact to Ferguson (OKC).
McCaw (TOR) cleanly dislodges the ball prior to making incidental body contact with Nader (OKC).
Ibaka (TOR) does not establish a legal picking position as he steps into Ferguson (OKC), turns his shoulder, and delivers contact that affects Ferguson's ability to defend the play.

Paul (OKC) ends his dribble and then loses control of the ball because Lowry (TOR) makes contact with it.  A player may dribble a second time if he lost control of the ball because of an opponent touching the ball.
Davis (TOR) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is taken.
Ferguson (OKC) moves laterally into VanVleet's (TOR) path and delivers contact that affects VanVleet's SQBR.
Ibaka (TOR) and Adams (OKC) briefly engage with each other as Adams begins to roll to the basket. After engaging with each other, both Ibaka and Adams disengage.
Lowry (TOR) slightly steps into Paul (OKC), but the contact is marginal as Paul is able to maintain his dribble and start his drive.
VanVleet (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC).
VanVleet (TOR) makes a natural drive to the basket and does not extend his arm as he and Dort (OKC) come together at the end of the drive.
Ibaka (TOR) gets his right foot down firming up as Dort (OKC) moves into Ibaka initiating the contact during the pick.
Adams (OKC) maintains a legal guarding position during the jump shot attempt by VanVleet (TOR).
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) is in the lane for longer then three seconds without actively guarding an opponent.
Davis (TOR) makes some lower body contact with Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC), but doesn't affect his ability to control the rebound.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) maintains a legal pivot foot.
Davis (TOR) moves alongside Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path toward the basket and makes marginal contact during the drive.
After Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) passes the ball, he moves into Lowry (TOR), who has established a legal defensive position, and the two make incidental contact.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) gathers the ball and takes two legal steps prior to his pass.
VanVleet (TOR) commits a take foul on Paul (OKC).
Ferguson (OKC) is awarded a timeout prior to the count reaching five seconds during the inbound.
As McCaw (TOR) attempts a take foul, he does not make contact with Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC).
